            <div class="kingster-page-title-wrap  kingster-style-custom kingster-left-align" style="background-image: url(../upload/fifth-boy-gaze.jpg) ;">
                <div class="kingster-header-transparent-substitute"></div>
                <div class="kingster-page-title-overlay"></div>
                <div class="kingster-page-title-bottom-gradient"></div>
                <div class="kingster-page-title-container kingster-container">
                    <div class="kingster-page-title-content kingster-item-pdlr" style="padding-top: 550px ;padding-bottom: 60px ;">
                        <div class="kingster-page-caption" style="font-size: 21px ;font-weight: 400 ;letter-spacing: 0px ;"></div>
                        <h1 class="kingster-page-title" style="font-size: 48px ;font-weight: 700 ;text-transform: none ;letter-spacing: 0px ;color: #ffffff ;">Continuous Enrollment</h1></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="kingster-breadcrumbs">
                <div class="kingster-breadcrumbs-container kingster-container">
                    <div class="kingster-breadcrumbs-item kingster-item-pdlr"> <span property="itemListElement" typeof="ListItem"><a property="item" typeof="WebPage" title="Stonehaven Home" href="../index.html" class="home"><span property="name">Home</span></a>
                        <meta property="position" content="1">
                        </span>&gt;<span property="itemListElement" typeof="ListItem"><a property="item" typeof="WebPage" title="Admissions Process" href="../index.html" class="home"><span property="name">Admissions</span></a>
                        <meta property="position" content="2">
			</span>&gt;<span property="itemListElement" typeof="ListItem"><span property="name">Continuous Enrollment</span>
                        </span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
	    <div class="kingster-page-wrapper" id="kingster-page-wrapper">
                <div class="gdlr-core-page-builder-body">

                    <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-wrapper " style="padding: 10px 0px 50px 0px;">
                        <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-background-wrap"></div>
                        <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-wrapper-content gdlr-core-js ">
                            <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-wrapper-container clearfix gdlr-core-container">

                                <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-30 gdlr-core-column-first">
                                    <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js ">
                                        <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js ">

                                	    <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element">
                                    		<div class="gdlr-core-text-box-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb gdlr-core-left-align" style="padding-bottom: 0px ;">
                                        	    <div class="kingster-single-article-content">
					  		<p>Wanting to simplify how families re-enroll their children, Stonehaven uses a process called Continuous Enrollment. In fact, there is no need at all to re-enroll. Once your children are enrolled, they are continuously enrolled until graduation from Stonehaven or the family follows an opt-out procedure.</p>
					  		<p>To state the process as simply as possible:</p>
					  		<p><ul><li>As part of the first-time enrollment process for new students, parents will indicate their understanding that their children are continuously enrolled at Stonehaven until graduation or, if necessary, the opt-out process is followed.</li><li>In March, a $500 Continuous Enrollment fee per family will be automatically charged via FACTS and applied towards next year's tuition.</li><li>Once enrolled, students are considered part of Stonehaven until they graduate with no further annual "re-enrollment" process involved.</li></ul></p>
					  		<p>We have created a list of Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) to help our families understand how this process works.</p>
					  		<p>The introduction of this process has been well-received at Stonehaven. The message we want to send is this: we want your children to receive a Christ-centered and classical education for many years to come and will make their continued enrollment as easy and seamless as possible.</p>
                                        	    </div>
                                    		</div>
                                	    </div>
					    <div class="gdlr-core-personnel-list-column  gdlr-core-column-60 gdlr-core-column-first gdlr-core-item-pdlr">
                                                <div class="gdlr-core-personnel-list clearfix">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <img src="../images/teachers/hmiley.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="200" title="Hannah Miley" />
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-personnel-list-content-wrap">
                                                        <h3 class="gdlr-core-personnel-list-title" style="font-size: 23px ;font-weight: 700 ;letter-spacing: 0px ;text-transform: none ;"><p>Hannah Miley</p></h3>
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-personnel-info">
                                                            <div class="kingster-personnel-info-list kingster-type-email"> <i class="kingster-personnel-info-list-icon fa fa-envelope-open"></i>  admissions@stonehavenschool.org</div>
                                                            <div class="kingster-personnel-info-list kingster-type-phone"> <i class="kingster-personnel-info-list-icon fa fa-phone"></i>  (770) 874-8885 (ext. 211)</div>
                                                        </div>
						    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>

                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
			
                                <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column gdlr-core-column-30">
                                    <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content-margin gdlr-core-js " style="padding: 0px 10px 0px 0px;">
                                        <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-column-content clearfix gdlr-core-js ">
                                            <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element">
                                                <div class="gdlr-core-title-item gdlr-core-item-pdb clearfix  gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-title-item-caption-top gdlr-core-item-pdlr" style="padding-bottom: 35px ;">
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-title-item-title-wrap clearfix">
                                                        <h3 class="gdlr-core-title-item-title gdlr-core-skin-title " style="font-size: 24px ;font-weight: 600 ;letter-spacing: 0px ;text-transform: none ;color: #1a1a1a ;">Frequently Asked Questions</h3></div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="gdlr-core-pbf-element">
                                                <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item gdlr-core-item-pdlr gdlr-core-item-pdb  gdlr-core-accordion-style-background-title-icon gdlr-core-left-align gdlr-core-icon-pos-right">
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix  gdlr-core-active">
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon "></div>
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper">
                                                            <h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-e-content">What is Continuous Enrollment?</h4>
                                                            <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content">
                                                                <p><ul><li>Continuous Enrollment is a common-sense approach to enrollment which is followed by almost all colleges and is being adopted by many Christian schools nation-wide.</li><li>Rather than an opt-IN annual re-enrollment process, Continuous Enrollment is an opt-OUT process. In other words, if you're returning to Stonehaven after initially enrolling, you’ll never have to worry about re-enrolling.</li></ul></p>
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix ">
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon "></div>
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper">
                                                            <h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-e-content">What is the Continuous Enrollment annual timeline?</h4>
                                                            <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content">
                                                                <p><ul><li>January - tuition is published for the upcoming year. Opt-out period begins</li><li>February - Indexed Tuition application period begins. Opt-out period ends February 28</li><li>March - Continuous Enrollment fee is withdrawn via FACTS for all enrolled students, unless an opt-out form is received</li></ul></p>
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix ">
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon "></div>
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper">
                                                            <h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-e-content">Does our family need a FACTS account?</h4>
                                                            <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content">
                                                                <p><ul><li>Yes, all families will need to have a FACTS account for monthly tuition collection. In addition to automatically collecting tuition payments, FACTS manages the collection of the Continuous Enrollment fee and other fees as needed.</li><li>Those families who already have a FACTS account do not need to register for one again. Those who do not should do so in January or February. The process is online and simple.</li><li>Families who are on a one- or three-payment plan may submit their tuition payments directly to the Stonehaven business office without using FACTS. However, the Continuous Enrollment fee will be collected through FACTS unless specific arrangements are made with the business office.</li></ul></p>
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix ">
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon "></div>
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper">
                                                            <h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-e-content">Is the Continuous Enrollment fee refundable?</h4>
                                                            <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content">
								<p>Yes, but only in the following cases:</p><p><ul><li>If your family submits an <a href="https://forms.gle/UXgY6scbotuXxzgRA" class="linker"><u>opt-out</u></a> form by Feb 28 (in which case the fee will not be drawn)</li><li>In the event of a move out of the area before school begins</li><li>In the event that Stonehaven can no longer meet your child’s educational needs</li><li>In the event that Stonehaven asks your child to withdraw</li><li>In the event that your Indexed Tuition amount is insufficient, after Stonehaven reviews your FACTS application with you to consider extenuating circumstances</li><li>In the event that there are unforeseen circumstances, in which case a refund needs Board approval</li></ul></p>
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                    <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix ">
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon "></div>
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper">
                                                            <h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-e-content">How do I opt out of Continuous Enrollment?</h4>
                                                            <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content">
								<p><ul><li>January and February are the opt-out months for current Stonehaven families. During that time, families who need to opt-out of Continuous Enrollment may do so by filling out an online opt-out form, <a href="https://forms.gle/UXgY6scbotuXxzgRA" class="linker"><u>found here.</u></a></li></ul></p>
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
					            <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-tab clearfix ">
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-icon gdlr-core-js gdlr-core-skin-icon "></div>
                                                        <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content-wrapper">
                                                            <h4 class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-title gdlr-core-js  gdlr-core-skin-e-background gdlr-core-skin-e-content">What if I opt out and later decide to re-enroll?</h4>
                                                            <div class="gdlr-core-accordion-item-content">
  								<p><ul><li>Families who opt-out and later decide to re-enroll will be considered for enrollment along with new applicants and according to space available.</li></ul></p>
                                                            </div>
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>

                                    </div>
                                </div>

                            </div>
                        </div>
